# Leadstodeals Scoring — Cursor Rules

Project stack: **Vite + React 19 + Tailwind CSS v4 + Supabase + React Router**.
This is **NOT a Next.js project**. Do not add `"use client"` directives, `next/*` imports, or App Router patterns.

---

## Known bugs & gotchas — READ BEFORE TOUCHING THESE AREAS

### 1. Never wrap `<App />` in `<StrictMode>` (Supabase auth lock deadlock)

`@supabase/supabase-js` uses a `localStorage` lock to serialize access to the
auth token. React `<StrictMode>` double-mounts components, so the second mount
tries to acquire a lock the first mount still holds. The lock waits 5 seconds
before forcefully recovering, during which `supabase.auth.getSession()` hangs,
`AuthContext` stays in `loading: true`, and `ProtectedRoute` shows a spinner
on the dark background — looking exactly like a broken black screen on refresh.

**Rule:** `src/main.jsx` must render `<App />` directly, no `<StrictMode>` wrapper.

```jsx
// ✅ Correct
createRoot(document.getElementById('root')).render(<App />)

// ❌ Breaks refresh on protected routes
createRoot(document.getElementById('root')).render(
  <StrictMode><App /></StrictMode>
)
```

### 2. `AuthContext` — NEVER call supabase inside `onAuthStateChange` callback (auth-lock deadlock)

The `onAuthStateChange` callback runs **inside** the `@supabase/gotrue-js`
auth lock. Any `supabase.from(...)` / `supabase.auth.*` call awaited
**inside** the callback tries to re-acquire the same lock and hangs forever.
Symptom: app stuck in `loading: true`, `ProtectedRoute` shows the spinner on
the dark background, you see this as a **black screen on refresh**. The CORS
errors from `writeScoresToHubSpot` disappearing is the tell — the app never
gets far enough to fire them.

**Rule:** the callback must be **synchronous** (no `async`, no `await`) and
must **defer** any further Supabase calls with `setTimeout(..., 0)`.
`fetchTenant` must own its own `try/catch` and always return, and the
deferred block ends with `.finally(() => setLoading(false))` so the spinner
always clears.

```jsx
// ✅ Correct
supabase.auth.onAuthStateChange((event, session) => {
  setUser(session?.user ?? null);
  if (session?.user) {
    setTimeout(() => {
      fetchTenant(session.user.id).finally(() => setLoading(false));
    }, 0);
  } else {
    setTenant(null);
    setLoading(false);
  }
});

// ❌ Deadlocks the auth-lock → black screen on refresh
supabase.auth.onAuthStateChange(async (event, session) => {
  if (session?.user) await fetchTenant(session.user.id); // hangs
  setLoading(false);
});
```

`fetchTenant` must also explicitly handle `data === null` (user has no
tenant row) and use `data?.tenants ?? null`.

Reference: https://supabase.com/docs/reference/javascript/auth-onauthstatechange

### 3. Supabase queries: `.single()` is dangerous

`.single()` throws 406 when 0 rows or >1 rows are returned. Always prefer:

- `.maybeSingle()` — returns `null` if no rows, throws only on multiple.
- `.limit(1).maybeSingle()` — safe when multiple rows are possible.

### 4. `vercel.json` rewrite must exclude static assets

For SPA routing on Vercel, the rewrite source **must not** match files with
extensions, otherwise `/assets/index-xxx.js` and `.css` get rewritten to
`/index.html` and the bundle never loads.

```json
{
  "rewrites": [
    {
      "source": "/:path((?!.*\\.[a-z0-9]+$).*)",
      "destination": "/index.html"
    }
  ]
}
```

Do NOT use `/(.*)` as source.

### 5. Multi-tenant proxy — never call HubSpot directly from the browser

All HubSpot API calls go through `leadstodeals-admin` at
`VITE_API_URL/proxy/hubspot/*`. The browser sends `X-Tenant-ID` header; the
proxy reads `tenants.hubspot_access_token` from Supabase (service key) and
forwards the call. Tokens never reach the browser.

---

## Conventions

- Tailwind v4 — use arbitrary values sparingly, prefer design tokens.
- All DB access through `src/lib/supabase.js` singleton.
- Scoring logic lives in `src/lib/scoringEngine.js` — 4 criterion types:
  `enum`, `range`, `province_map`, `sector_map`. Each criterion row in
  Supabase has `type TEXT` and `config JSONB` columns.
- Score formula: `((Σ(weight × multiplier) + totalWeights) / (totalWeights × 2)) × 100`, bounded 0–100.
- Historical scores are **INSERTED** (not upserted) into `deal_scores` so we
  keep a timeline.
